    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "The reason this happens is because the full list of items of infiniteHits is stored inside infiniteHits itself, not somewhere global, meaning that geo search doesn't have access to that.\r\n\r\nA workaround could be to use useGeoSearch for the boundaries etc, but still use useInfiniteHits for displaying the hits on the map, as you can still access _geoLoc.\r\n\r\nWould that work for your use case?",
